      <p>Face it, hip pain can be caused by a myriad of issues, that's why it is best to have a healthcare provider evaluate and diagnose symptoms through a physical exam and even imaging like MRI or ultrasound. Typically, a provider may suggest physical therapy exercises and easy walking, but it can be months before you get much relief. Some providers may suggest cortisone injections or even surgery in extreme circumstances if the tendon ruptures.</p>

